    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just hard to see the point in \"managing\" it. what's the point of managing a life that's already half-finished? it feels like i'm just an echo of who i used to be. if i'm just waiting to catch up to him, maybe i'm just delaying the inevitable. it would be so much easier to just stop fighting the emptiness and let it take over. does that even make sense? like, why is it so wrong to want the peace of finally being done with the noise?",
